==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Euryale
<hw>Eu*ry"a*le</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr.
<etsep>Euryale</etsep>, one of the Gorgons.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A genus of water lilies, growing in India and
China. The only species (<spn>Euryale ferox</spn>) is very prickly on
the peduncles and calyx. The rootstocks and seeds are used as
food.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zo⟦oum⟧l.)</fld> <def>A genus of ophiurans with
much-branched arms.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Euryalida</ent>⟦br⟧
\'d8
